>  [Hiremath, Vaibhav] Joel,
>
> I am bit surprised by this patch submission, first of all, the patch
> has been submitted without my knowledge. And I was not aware that you
> are targeting linux-media for this code-snippet.

This is an RFC, not a patch submission.

>
> This code needs lot of cleanup and changes to get to the level where we
> can submit it to the linux-media, and I think I clearly mentioned about
> known issues with this patch/driver in the commit itself. Please refer
> to the below commit -
>
> http://arago-project.org/git/projects/?p=linux-
> omap3.git;a=commitdiff;h=c6174e0658b9aaa8f7a3ec9fe562619084d34f59
>
> I agree that we had some internal discussion on this and I was under
> assumption that this effort was only towards beagle openembedded and
> not for linux-media.

This is just an attempt to try to help clean it up.  I think the patch for an older version of the kernel was already public.  This isn't intended to be placed on the linux-media git tree.  Many of the interested developers, however, may be on that list--and the code eventually needs to be made ready for inclusion on that git tree.  Again, this is an RFC, not a patch submission.

>
> I also agree with the fact that, due to other critical issues I could
> not able to spend time on this and upstream it. But as I mentioned to
> you in one of private discussion, now we are working to get all this
> patches upstream and soon you will see patches coming in from my team.

I was not aware this was in conflict.  That seems like exactly the reason we should be discussing this on the open external list--to avoid developers working redundantly on cleaning up patches for upstream.

>
> Another important side note, you should always retain original
> authorship of the patches/commits/signoffs. It should always be in
> incremental order from baseline, which you are using.

Very good point.  If this was not done properly, it seriously needs to be corrected.  Thanks for that valuable review comment on what is essentially code you authored, by my understanding.

I do see your name in the copyright comments below.  Where else is it missing?

Again, this was not submitted for inclusion into upstream trees--so I believe it is appropriate to get these corrections via the e-mail chain.

>
> Thanks,
> Vaibhav
